{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1769701576,"nonce":"F+OM9/ZRq02u2vuda8w8jRY9ZQM=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87mwBqU","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/118","origin":"github"},"title":"Prevent documentation hallucinations with code validation workflow","message":"## Problem Statement\n\nRecent AI-generated documentation in external repositories (e.g., rolker/unh_marine_autonomy PR #37) demonstrated systematic hallucinations that undermined documentation quality:\n\n- **13 code review comments** flagged inaccuracies\n- **Non-existent parameters** documented (e.g., `update_rate`, `standby_enabled`)\n- **Wrong message types** (e.g., `marine_interfaces` vs actual `marine_nav_interfaces`, `project11_msgs`)\n- **Fabricated API signatures** (e.g., `PilotingMode` fields that don't exist)\n- **Incorrect implementation details** (e.g., `timerCallback()` that doesn't exist in code)\n- **Wrong command formats** (e.g., `replace` vs actual `replace_task`)\n\n**Root Cause**: AI agents generated documentation based on assumptions and typical ROS2 patterns rather than inspecting actual source code.\n\n**Reference**: https://github.com/rolker/unh_marine_autonomy/pull/37 (see review comments for examples)\n\n---\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\nImplement a multi-phase approach to enforce code-based documentation generation:\n\n### Phase 1: Enhanced Agent Instructions (Immediate)\n\n**Deliverable**: Update `.agent/AI_RULES.md` and documentation-specific instructions\n\n**New Rules**:\n- ✅ **MUST** grep actual source code for parameters before documenting them\n- ✅ **MUST** verify message types in `package.xml`/`CMakeLists.txt` dependencies\n- ✅ **MUST** extract API signatures from actual C++/Python source files\n- ✅ **MUST** cite source file + line numbers for all documented items\n- ❌ **NEVER** document based on assumptions or \"typical ROS2 patterns\"\n\n**Example Workflow**:\n```bash\n# Before documenting a node's parameters:\ngrep -r \"declare_parameter\" src/my_package/src/my_node.cpp\n\n# Before documenting message types:\ngrep -r \"project11_msgs\" src/my_package/package.xml\n```\n\n---\n\n### Phase 2: Documentation Templates with Validation Hooks (Short-term)\n\n**Deliverable**: Create `.agent/templates/documentation/` with structured templates\n\n**Templates**:\n1. **`interface_documentation.md.template`**\n   - Checklist for each topic/service/action:\n     - [ ] Message type verified in package.xml\n     - [ ] Publisher/subscriber verified in source code\n     - [ ] Source citation: `file.cpp:line_number`\n\n2. **`api_documentation.md.template`**\n   - Table format requiring:\n     - API element (class/function/parameter)\n     - Source file citation\n     - Extracted signature from code\n     - Purpose (inferred from code context)\n\n3. **`node_documentation.md.template`**\n   - Parameters section requires:\n     - Parameter name from `declare_parameter()` call\n     - Type from source code\n     - Default value from source code\n     - Source citation\n\n**Enforcement**: Agents must fill all citations before documentation PR is considered complete.\n\n---\n\n### Phase 3: Automated Validation Script (Medium-term)\n\n**Deliverable**: `.agent/scripts/validate_docs.py` with pre-commit integration\n\n**Functionality**:\n```python\n# Parse documentation files for claims\n# Cross-reference against actual source code\n# Report potential hallucinations\n\nExample Output:\n❌ docs/interfaces.md:149 - Service type 'marine_interfaces/TaskManagerCmd' \n   not found in dependencies (found: mission_manager_interfaces/TaskManagerCmd)\n   \n❌ docs/autonomy_modes.md:195 - Parameter 'update_rate' documented \n   but not found in helm_manager source code\n   \n✅ docs/interfaces.md:55 - Topic 'project11/status/mission_manager' \n   verified as project11_msgs/Heartbeat in camp_interface.cpp:123\n```\n\n**Integration**:\n- Add to `pre-commit-config.yaml`\n- Run on all `docs/**/*.md` files\n- Fail commit if hallucinations detected\n- Provide fix suggestions when possible\n\n---\n\n### Phase 4: Knowledge Base Enhancement (Ongoing)\n\n**Deliverable**: Auto-generated ground truth files in `.agent/knowledge/`\n\n**Files**:\n1. **`ros_interfaces_registry.yaml`**\n   ```yaml\n   # Auto-generated during colcon build\n   packages:\n     marine_nav_interfaces:\n       messages:\n         - TaskInformation\n         - TaskFeedback\n       services:\n         - TaskManagerCmd\n       actions:\n         - RunTasks\n         - ComputeSonarCoveragePath\n   ```\n\n2. **`node_parameters_inventory.yaml`**\n   ```yaml\n   # Extracted from source code\n   helm_manager:\n     source: src/helm_manager.cpp\n     parameters:\n       - name: output_type\n         type: string\n         default: \"helm\"\n         line: 45\n       - name: max_speed\n         type: double\n         default: 2.5\n         line: 48\n   ```\n\n**Update Mechanism**:\n- Run extraction script during `make build`\n- Store in git-ignored `.agent/knowledge/generated/`\n- Agents check these files before documenting interfaces\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Milestone 1: Quick Wins (1-2 days)\n- [ ] Add documentation validation rules to `.agent/AI_RULES.md`\n- [ ] Create basic `interface_documentation.md.template`\n- [ ] Document validation workflow in `.agent/knowledge/ros2_documentation_best_practices.md`\n\n### Milestone 2: Tooling (1 week)\n- [ ] Implement `validate_docs.py` with basic checks:\n  - Parameter existence validation\n  - Message type package validation\n  - Source citation format validation\n- [ ] Add pre-commit hook integration\n- [ ] Test on PR #37 documentation (should catch all 13 issues)\n\n### Milestone 3: Automation (2 weeks)\n- [ ] Build interface registry extractor\n- [ ] Build parameter inventory extractor\n- [ ] Integrate with `make build` workflow\n- [ ] Update agent instructions to reference generated knowledge\n\n### Milestone 4: Validation (Ongoing)\n- [ ] Re-generate documentation for test case (unh_marine_autonomy interfaces)\n- [ ] Verify 0 hallucinations in generated docs\n- [ ] Store successful patterns as examples in `.agent/examples/`\n\n---\n\n## Success Metrics\n\n- **Zero hallucinations**: Re-running PR #37 documentation workflow produces 0 review comments about inaccuracies\n- **Code coverage**: 100% of documented parameters/interfaces have source citations\n- **Automation**: `validate_docs.py` catches at least 90% of common hallucination patterns\n- **Developer confidence**: Documentation trusted as accurate reference for integration work\n\n---\n\n## Related Files\n\n- `.agent/AI_RULES.md` - Core agent workflow rules\n- `.agent/knowledge/ros2_development_patterns.md` - ROS2 conventions\n- `pre-commit-config.yaml` - Pre-commit hook configuration\n- `layers/*/src/` - Source code to validate against","files":null}]}